Materials and methods
In this work, we report our experiences of training 24 motor-disabled participants at rehabilitation clinics or at the end-users{\textquoteright} homes, without BCI experts present. We also share the lessons that we have learned through transferring BCI technologies from the lab to the user's home or clinics.
Results
